Dotfiles - Michael Gharbi <gharbi@mit.edu>
------------------------------------------

* Clone the repository as ~/.dotfiles then make symlinks to its content from the
user directory.


* Fork oh-my-zsh, snipmate and others for customizations

* Installing vim/bundle/command-t:
    = requires vim compiled with ruby support e.g. homebrew version
    - cd vim/bundle/command-t
    - bundle install
    - rake make

* For iterm2, set 'Load preferences from a custom folder or URL' to
'/Users/username/.dotfiles/iterm2_settings/'

* Adding a sub-repository: git submodule add {url} {local_path}; git submodule
init; git submodule update

* Clang-complete requires the Clang compiler

* Jedi-Vim for Python requires: pip install jedi


